Description: Iron leaf-shaped spear-head with a wrapped socket
Curator's comments: One of "several lance-heads" mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 77 § 77, p. 110, pl. xxxvii, 4. see also pieces Bolton, 1886.28.22.i-j and deaccessioned Boston, MFA, 87.523, 87.524.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 77 § 77, p. 110, pl. xxxvii, 4)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.46, p.73, p.184, pl.26)
